        <title>
            Nabla : Development Guide : Content Services
        </title>
    </properties>
    <body>
        <section name="Create a new ContentService">
        <subsection name="DÃ©finition">
            <p>
                A content service can create its own pages. Each service has a call parameter which
                allows the portal to dispatch requests towards the service. Nabla uses various 
                Content Services as enumerated below :
            </p>
            <p>
            <table>
                <tr>
                    <th>Service</th>
                    <th>Parameter</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>PageService</td>
                    <td>id_page</td>
                    <td>Construction Service and diplay of Nabla pages</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>ArticleService</td>
                    <td>id_article</td>
                    <td>Construction Service and diplay of Nabla pages</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>SearchService</td>
                    <td>query</td>
                    <td>Nabla Search Service</td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>XPageService</td>
                    <td>page</td>
                    <td>Nabla's XPages application container</td>
                </tr>
            </table>
            </p>
        </subsection>
        <subsection name="Interfacing the ContentService">
            <p>
                Here are the interface methods of the ContentService : 
            </p>
            <p>
                <table>
                    <tr>
                        <th>Method</th>
                        <th>Description</th>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>getName</td>
                        <td>
                             Return the name of the Content Service.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>isInvoked</td>
                        <td>
                             Resolves from the parameters from the HTTP request,
                             whether it is addessed to t.For example, the PageService 
                             verifies if the request includes the <code>id_page</code> parameter. 
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>getCache</td>
                        <td>
                             Indicates if the service has a cache activated. 
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>getCacheSize</td>
                        <td>
                             Returns the number of objects in the cache.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>getPage</td>
                        <td>
                            Builds a page by using the request parameters and mode.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
                        <td>resetCache</td>
                        <td>
                             Empties the cache of the content service.
                        </td>
                    </tr>
                </table>
            </p>
        </subsection>
        <subsection name="Creation of ContentService" >
            <p>
                New services can be added by new plugins. The plugin must define
                must define the ContentService in its deployment file as described
                below :
                            
            </p>
            <p>
                <div class="source">
                    <pre>
   &lt;!-- Content Service --&gt;
   &lt;content-service&gt;
     &lt;content-service-class&gt;com.nabla.project.plugins.myplugin.service.MyContentService&lt;/content-service-class&gt;
   &lt;/content-service&gt;                     
                    </pre>
                </div>
            </p>
            
        </subsection>
        </section>
